 President Kenyatta spoke at the event, praising the Ministry of Education and the KNEC team for conducting credible national exams despite the school calendar disruptions caused by the Covid-19 pandemic. Dr. Joseph Kinyua, the Head of Public Service, Dr. Fred Matiang'i, the Interior Cabinet Secretary, Teachers Service Commission CEO Nancy Macharia, KNEC Chairman John Onsati, and the council's Chief Executive Officer David Njeng'ere were all present at the meeting. Over 1.2 million students sat their KCPE exams this year, from 28,213 examinations across the country. 